cs.SC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.LO, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing and manipulating symbolic expressions, specifically Ore operators with polynomial coefficients. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents algorithms for contraction and desingularization of D-finite functions and systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with linear homogeneous partial differential equations and their solution spaces. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the properties and applications of completely desingularized operators. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with certifying integer sequences and checking special cases of a conjecture.
